# Server Data Patterns

Data flows through Next.js Server Components and Server Actions. Do not fetch database data from Client Components or Route Handlers when a Server Component or Server Action can handle it.

## Rules

1. **Reads** — fetch data in Server Components (pages, layouts, or server-only child components). Pass results as props to Client Components.
2. **Writes** — all `insert`, `update`, and `delete` operations go through Server Actions (`"use server"`). Do not mutate the database from Client Components, Route Handlers, or client-side fetch calls.
3. **Validation** — validate all input with [Zod](https://zod.dev). Define schemas once and reuse them for parsing and TypeScript types.
4. **Server Action signatures** — accept a typed object (e.g. `CreateDeckInput`), never `FormData` as the parameter type. Parse with Zod inside the action before touching the database.

## Conventions

- Colocate Zod schemas with their Server Actions (e.g. `src/app/actions/decks.ts`) or in a shared `src/lib/schemas/` module when reused.
- Derive input types with `z.infer<typeof schema>` — do not duplicate types by hand.
- Client Components call Server Actions directly; convert form values to a plain object before invoking the action.
- Combine with [clerk-auth.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/clerk-auth.mdc) — call `auth()` in every Server Action and scope mutations to the signed-in user.
- Combine with [drizzle-database.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/drizzle-database.mdc) — use the shared `db` instance and schema tables for all queries.

## Examples

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — fetch in a Client Component
"use client";
useEffect(() => {
  fetch("/api/decks").then((r) => r.json()).then(setDecks);
}, []);

// ❌ BAD — database mutation in a Route Handler
export async function POST(req: Request) {
  const body = await req.json();
  await db.insert(decksTable).values(body);
}

// ❌ BAD — FormData as the action parameter type
export async function createDeck(formData: FormData) {
  const title = formData.get("title") as string;
  await db.insert(decksTable).values({ title, userId });
}

// ❌ BAD — no Zod validation
export async function createDeck(input: { title: string }) {
  await db.insert(decksTable).values(input);
}
```

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — read in a Server Component
export default async function DecksPage() {
  const { userId } = await auth();
  if (!userId) redirect("/sign-in");

  const decks = await db
    .select()
    .from(decksTable)
    .where(eq(decksTable.userId, userId));

  return <DeckList decks={decks} />;
}
```

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — typed input, Zod validation, Server Action mutation
"use server";

import { z } from "zod";
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";
import { eq } from "drizzle-orm";
import { db } from "@/db";
import { decksTable } from "@/db/schema";

const createDeckSchema = z.object({
  title: z.string().trim().min(1).max(100),
});

type CreateDeckInput = z.infer<typeof createDeckSchema>;

export async function createDeck(input: CreateDeckInput) {
  const { userId } = await auth();
  if (!userId) throw new Error("Unauthorized");

  const { title } = createDeckSchema.parse(input);

  await db.insert(decksTable).values({ title, userId });
}
```

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — Client Component passes a typed object to the action
"use client";

import { createDeck } from "@/app/actions/decks";

function CreateDeckForm() {
  async function onSubmit(title: string) {
    await createDeck({ title });
  }
  // ...
}
```
